  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "They developed six alternative solutions based on the choices of (1) whether to use hand-crafted language features, word embeddings or a combination thereof for classification, (2) whether pre-trained language models like BERT are a viable replacement for the more traditional techniques, and (3) whether a mashup of existing (and often generic) NLP tools would be adequate for specific RE tasks.",
    "Wang et al.",
    "[52,53] proposed a deep context-wise semantic technique to resolve entity co-reference in natural-language requirements, which consists of two parts.",
    "One is a deep fine-tuned BERT context model for context representation, and the other is a Word2Vec-based entity network for entity representation.",
    "Then they proposed to utilize a multi-layer perceptron (MLP) to fuse two representations."
  ],
